While no court rule in the State of Mayflower governs the standard for temporary restraining orders, statute provides that this Court “may issue all writs necessary or appropriate in aid of ... [its] respective jurisdiction[] and agreeable to the usages and principles of law.” 5 M.S.C. 1 § 1401.1.

This Court should grant a TRO because, as alleged in the Complaint, the regulation that Defendant is enforcing is blatantly unconstitutional under Mansky's vagueness standard. I thus have a strong likelihood of succeeding on the merits.

Furthermore, the enforcement of this regulation, as alleged in the Complaint, prevents DonaldMc's from using its very profitable “shock marketing" strategy. DonaldMc's will incur financial harm if the unconstitutional restriction remains enforced, as it will have to adopt a less profitable or more experimental marketing strategy, potentially alienating its existing customer base.
